name: Vintage Indigo Beige
title: New Balance 550 Vintage Indigo Beige
description:
The New Balance 550 Vintage Indigo Beige is a retro-inspired sneaker that was released as part of the sports collection by the American brand.

This sneaker features a beige and white mesh and leather upper with hints of vintage indigo on the tongues, ankles, and branding. Other details include the trademark "N" logo on the sides, "550" labeling on the laterals, New Balance basketball branding on the tongue tag, midsole and heel, and a lace-up closing system. The design is finished with a white midsole that sits on an Indigo rubber outsole with a linear pattern.

The New Balance 550 Vintage Indigo Beige made its debut on December 14th, 2022, retailing at $110.

name: Indigo (Women's)
title: Nike Blazer Mid 77 Indigo (Women's)
description:
The Nike Blazer Mid 77 Indigo (W) is part of a Nike collection that pays homage to the Indigofera Tinctoria plant, commonly referred to as True Indigo. This women's sneaker features a white upper constructed using breathable canvas with synthetic suede overlays and an embroidered Indigo plant graphic. On its upper, it has a light blue swoosh and a light blue heel tab engraved with True Indigo’s scientific information. Furthermore, it boasts a white midsole and a rubber outsole.

The women's Nike Blazer Mid 77 Indigo (W) was released on 15th June 2021. It retailed at $110.

name: Quai 54 (2022)
title: Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Utility Stash Quai 54 (2022)
description:
The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Utility Stash Quai 54 2022 comes from a collaboration between the Nike Jordan brand and Quai 54.

The silhouette adds heft to the design by introducing pouches at the Swooshes and heel. Canvas is used for the upper in this "Quai 54" colorway, with white overlays sitting on top of a dark blue foundation. The details on the upper are done in this color scheme, and it is finished off with an orange outsole, orange sole stitching, and a red tag with collaboration branding.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Utility Stash Quai 54 2022 debuted on August 30, 2022, and retailed at $190.

name: Indigo (Women's)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Indigo (Women's)
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Indigo W is a sneaker model that comes in a combination of obsidian, white, and black color scheme.

An indigo plant that is visibly embroidered both on the left shoe of this pair at the back left, as well as on the back right of the right shoe, is where the name of this sneaker came from. The white canvas overlays all around its toebox, the light-blue-colored Nike Swoosh overlay on its sides, as well as the second light-blue-colored brand mark on its heels, are all features of this Nike Air Force 1 for women.

The Nike Air Force 1 Indigo W made its debut on the 15th of May 2021 and it had a recommended retail price of $110.

name: Indigo
title: Jordan 12 Retro Indigo
description:
Ever since Michael Jordan’s memorable 1997 Flu Game, the Air Jordan 12s have been a pinnacle addition to the Jordan Brand lineage. In 2020, the Air Jordan 12 Indigo brings back everything that Jordan heads love about the sneaker.

The Air Jordan 12 Indigo shares a striking resemblance to 2012’s Obsidian retro. Most Jordan 12 retros feature tumbled leather, but the Air Jordan 12 Stone Blue takes on smooth grain leather. Hits of white on the toebox and midsole add contrast to a majority Stone Blue sneaker. From there, the iconic Jumpman logo is seen on both stamped on the outsole and embroidered on the tongue. These sneakers released in August of 2020 and retailed for $190.

name: Natural Indigo
title: New Balance 9060 Natural Indigo
description: The New Balance 9060 Natural Indigo is a stylish and comfortable sneaker that is perfect for everyday wear. Made with high-quality materials, this shoe features a natural indigo colorway that is both unique and eye-catching. The upper is constructed from premium suede and mesh, while the midsole is made from lightweight REVlite foam for superior cushioning and support. The outsole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and grip on any surface. This sneaker was released on September 9th, 2022, with a retail price of $150. Whether you're hitting the streets or just running errands, the New Balance 9060 Natural Indigo is a must-have addition to your sneaker collection.

name: Quai 54
title: Jordan Luka 1 Quai 54
description: The Air Jordan Luka 1 Quai 54 is a highly anticipated release from the iconic brand. This sneaker features a sleek black and white colorway with pops of vibrant blue and red accents. The upper is constructed from premium leather and synthetic materials, providing durability and comfort. The shoe also boasts a responsive Air-Sole unit in the heel for added cushioning and support. The Quai 54 logo is prominently displayed on the tongue and heel, paying homage to the annual streetball tournament held in Paris. This limited edition sneaker was released on September 1, 2022, with a retail price of $110. Don't miss your chance to add this stylish and functional sneaker to your collection.

name: Quai 54 (2022)
title: Jordan 7 Retro Quai 54 (2022)
description: The Air Jordan 7 Retro Quai 54 2022 is a highly anticipated release from Jordan Brand. The shoe features a black and white colorway with hits of blue and red, paying homage to the annual Quai 54 basketball tournament held in Paris. The upper is constructed with a mix of leather and suede, while the midsole is equipped with Nike Air technology for added comfort. The outsole features a unique pattern inspired by African tribal art. The release date for the Air Jordan 7 Retro Quai 54 2022 is set for December 20th, 2022, with a retail price of $225. Don't miss out on this limited edition release that combines style and performance in one iconic silhouette.

name: Denim Sashiko
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Denim Sashiko
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Sashiko is part of a collection that highlights the intricacies of the Japanese style of embroidery for which the shoe is named. Sashiko is a Japanese word translated as "little stabs." Nike enthusiasts can see this stitching clearly all along the upper portion of the silhouette.

The bright white laces of the Nike SB Dunk Low Sashiko stand out against the Mystic Navy/Mystic Navy-Gum Light Brown-Sail colorway of the shoe, and the midsole matches this look to create a nice contrast between the brown outsole and the double tones of the suede upper. The tongue features a lighter denim around the outer edge and a darker version across the body, and the back part of the upper going to the ankle guard also sports the more subdued tone. The front portion of the Nike SB Dunk Low Sashiko features the lighter suede, and the special stitching starts here at the bottom of the toe box and continues to wrap the entire upper in wavy lines. Both Nike and Nike SB branding round out the design with a unique, intentionally incomplete "Swoosh" present on the sides of the shoes.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Sashiko released in August 2020 and retailed for $110.

name: Indigo
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 LV8 Indigo
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 07 LV8 Indigo has become a celebrated addition with a White, Obsidian-white and Black color scheme.

Built with a white leather upper, this LV8 Air Force model by Nike is highlighted by an Aqua Blue tone on the canvas that runs through the Nike Swoosh logos to the heel tab. Special details include scientific facts about the plant christened on the heel tab and a True Indigo plant embroidered on the tongue. A White midsole that rests on a Dark Cider rubber outsole completes the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 07 LV8 Indigo was made available on April 29, 2021. Initially, it retailed at $110.

name: Indiglo (2016)
title: Jordan 14 Retro Indiglo (2016)
description: The Air Jordan 14 Indiglo colorway first released in the summer of 1999. The OG Indiglo 14 was a unique colorway in that it was not attached to or inspired by a team colorway. In fact it was one of the earliest "Lifestyle" or "LS" colorways, though it was never officially labeled as such. The Air Jordan 14 was the last Jordan shoe that Michael Jordan wore on the court as a member of the Chicago Bulls. The Air Jordan 14 design inspiration came from the Ferrari that MJ was driving at the time. In fact, the logo on the ankle and font on the tongue were also inspired by the Ferrari's logo and emblems. The Indiglo Jordan 14 Retro brings back distant memories of that speed inspired era and adds a premium leather and nubuck that further tie in the luxurious sports car queues. The 2016 Air Jordan 14 Indiglo retail price was $190 and also released in Grade School sizes.

name: Tie Dye
title: Nike Air Max 97 Golf Tie Dye
description:
The Nike Air Max 97 Golf Tie Dye includes a useful hidden lacing system that adds to an already sleek design, and the wavy lines across the upper of the shoe enhance this visual effect. The official colorway for the Nike Air Max 97 Golf Tie Dye is Summit White/Lemon Venom-Indigo Fog-Deep Royal Blue, and the white shading provides an excellent base from which the other colors are able to shine. Some of the hidden gems of this silhouette include "Nike Golf" lettering inside the sole that is reminiscent of the same historical style of art from which the shoe takes its name. Fans will also notice that the bottom of the outsole spells "love" in large, colorful letters. The left and right shoes have slightly different color arrangements in their patterns to complete this unique look.

The Nike Air Max 97 Golf Tie Dye released in August 2020 and retailed for $190.

description: Whether you're looking to hit the pitch or pop an ollie, the Supreme Nike SB Gato is an ideal pair for both. The streetwear brand took the classic soccer silhouette and re-worked it into a skate shoe, with this version coming in a clean light armory blue, white and neutral indigo colorway. The sleek shoe sports a blue-based calfskin leather upper, lenticular side panels, a white "Swoosh" logo on the sides, "Supreme" branding throughout, a cushlon midsole, and a full gum rubber outsole. These dropped in August of 2018, where they were available exclusively in-store at all Supreme locations as well as online via their web shop. If you’re a fan of Nike SB’s and dig everything Supreme, then this pair is another must-have.
